{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is service + persistence handoff: summary-write logic must query stored per-dimension findings for the same round and reject PASS on conflict. Unit tests of a pure checker can miss wiring bugs (wrong round key, stale read, skipped query). Rejected System because behavior is about stored records and validation logic, not real OS/network/subprocess. Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness here does not depend on model output, only persisted verdict state.","test_description":"Run summary-save API/use-case against a real local test DB with seeded findings including at least one FAIL in the target round; attempt to persist PASS summary and assert write is rejected with conflict reason and no PASS summary committed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Bug was data-source selection across modules (gate trusted summary text). Minimum test must wire gate + storage to prove gate decision uses persisted findings, not manual summary field. Rejected higher levels: behavior text is deterministic data-read policy with no real infra or model-quality dependency.","test_description":"Seed DB with manual summary text saying PASS and stored per-dimension findings containing FAIL; execute stop-gate computation through normal service path and assert verdict is FAIL/escalate based on stored findings, even if summary text is PASS.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is cross-module policy enforcement (input flag parsing + persistence of audit record). Unit tests on flag parser miss missing/failed audit writes. Rejected System because local in-process DB/log sink is enough; rejected Agentic/Workflow because no model judgment is involved.","test_description":"Exercise summary submission endpoint/use-case in two cases: without override flag (manual override rejected) and with override flag (accepted but warning audit record written with actor, timestamp, round, reason). Verify persisted audit artifact exists and is queryable.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.71,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure is temporal/state correlation across modules: latest fix commit metadata must be compared to review-round provenance before PASS. Unit checks can miss wrong join/comparison path in repository/service wiring. Rejected System: behavior text does not require real git subprocess; commit/round metadata can be modeled in local DB. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: check is freshness/provenance constraint, not model output quality.","test_description":"Seed commit history metadata with a latest fix commit and only pre-fix review round IDs; run gate finalize and assert PASS blocked. Then add a post-fix round ID and assert PASS can proceed when other conditions pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires a real review-agent round in the live loop on updated diff. A stubbed agent completion can hide failures where orchestration marks rounds fresh without an actual model run. Rejected Workflow because this behavior needs one fresh post-fix agentic round gate, not necessarily multi-agentic sequencing for assertion.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end live loop test with real review-agent invocation on updated diff: attempt finalize without running post-fix round (must block), then run an actual post-fix agent round and verify finalize condition changes only after that round is recorded as fresh.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.24,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.55,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Decision is deterministic policy over stored results and round counters; minimum real failure boundary is orchestration between persistence + gate policy. Rejected Agentic/Workflow due explicit 'stored results' wording: test need not depend on live model outputs. Rejected System because no real OS/network/subprocess is required.","test_description":"Seed stored results with unresolved MUST-FIX findings and set review-round budget as exhausted; execute gate outcome computation through application service and assert escalation state is emitted and PASS is impossible.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.06}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings